2.title: Tyrant Unleashed
2.text: Welcome to the debut of Tyrant Unleashed - a gritty new strategy card game! Take down Typhon Vex and the Raiders in the single-player missions or dominate your opponents in Battle!

3.title: Patch 2 is here!
3.text: The latest update has added several performance improvements. The next patch will focus on Commanders, Artifacts, and Fusion. Stay tuned!

4.title: Patch 3: Commanders
4.text: The brand new Commander Tree is here! Now you can choose which Faction you align with through the new Commander Promotion tree. Click the Edit button under your Commander to see all the amazing new Commanders!

5.title: Kongregate Forums
5.text: Check out the new forums! Log into Kongregate by tapping the K button in the profile box. Once your account is synchronized to Kongregate, you'll be able to view the community forums, earn badges, and more!

6.title: New Update!
6.text: A new update is out, with much improved performance on low memory devices, improved UI, easier to tap buttons, and more! Stay tuned for improvements to the matchmaking system later this week.

7.title: Tartarus has Opened
7.text: Two new maps have opened up, beyond the Blightlands Nexus! Can you defeat the hordes of Tartarus? We have also further optimized performance on low-memory devices and updated the Battle UI.

8.title: Tartarus Unleashed!
8.text: Portals to Tartarus have been opened, and the grotesque Miasma awaits. Crush Miasma now to earn limited-time rewards!

9.title: The portal is closing...
9.text: The portals have become unstable. Finish the Tartarus Depths now before they close forever!

10.title: The Depths sealed
10.text: The Depths have been sealed. Congratulations to all who bested Miasma and Gore Typhon!

11.title: Guilds, new Fusion cards
11.text: Guilds are now out across all platforms! Team up with friends and discuss strategies. Guild battles will be coming soon! We have also introduced 15 explosive new Fusion recipes for Epic and Legendary cards.

12.title: Harvest of Carnage
12.text: Typhon's Raiders are back for revenge! Massive machines of war are roaming the Wasteland, unearthed from the remnants of the old Asphodel Empire. Defend the Nexus before the Raiders destroy Acheron!

13.title: The Tyr Cannon
13.text: The Raiders' march towards the Wasteland Nexus is now joined by the Tyr Cannon, a massive tank capable of leveling cities in a single blast. Commander, you must not let them reach the Nexus!

14.title: Limited Time
14.text: Check out the new limited time Fusion Pack and Salvage Coins from the Store - available until all weekend-long!

15.title: Rise of the Ancients
15.text: An excavation in Arctis reveals an ancient secret that could save, or destroy, the entire world. Defeat the Righteous protectors and uncover the mysterious origins of Acheron.

16.title: Acheron Solstice
16.text: The Progenitors have been unearthed! These ancient creatures have an alignment with all other Factions, and will be boosted by ALL faction-specific skills!

17.title: Exodus War is Coming
17.text: The Exodus War approaches! This Friday, team up with your guildmates to crush the opposition on the alien Xeno homeworld. But beware... noxious fumes will make even a seasoned veteran susceptible to poison...

18.title: Exodus War is over
18.text: The Exodus War has ended. Congratulations to the top guilds! Soon, discover the dark history behind the Phobos Orbital Station...

19.title: Healing Light
19.text: The next Guild War is approaching! Starting March 14th, Guilds will experience an enhancement to Healing and the introduction of Fortresses!

20.title: Tides of War
20.text: The last chapter of Phobos has arrived, and a new war is coming. Earn new Guild Points (GP) from completing the event Objectives and help your guild upgrade it's Fortress! Note: this Fortress will only last until the end of the War Weekend.

21.title: Massive Invasion
21.text: The Xeno Worldship approaches to conquer Acheron. Head to the Worldship location on the map and put a stop to it. Recruit help from the Portal Box in the store!

22.title: Shattered Worldship
22.text: The Worldship has crashed down to Acheron and all Factions must race to salvage the mysterious Xeno tech. Worldship Shattered War starts May 9th. Don't let the carnage drive you Berserk.

23.title: Worldship Infested
23.text: The Imperials arrive at the Worldship crash site only to find that Bloodthirsty have consumed everything. Can you overcome this menace before it engulfs Acheron? The Infested Worldship event has begun. Recruit help from the new style event box, the Wreckage Box; featuring the new skill Corrosive!

24.title: Worldship Infested 2
24.text: The Kraken has fallen but the Blightbloom looms ahead. Defeat it before it transforms the area into a toxic paradise for Bloodthirsty.

25.title: Worldship Infested 3
25.text: Witness the end to the Worldship Infested chapter as Bloodthirsty beasts and Xeno tech merge into a terrifying enemy. Recruit help from the Sacrifce Box to lead you on the path to victory. Or try your hand at Razogoth Mutant, a brutally difficult side boss that will leave you shaking with fear.

26.title: Eradication War
26.text: Packs of Xeno-tech fused Bloodthirsty remain as evil factions try to harness their power for themselves. Gather reinforcements from the Eradicate Box and stop them before it is too late!

27.title: Asphodel Garrison
27.text: Asphodel is under Siege! Witness the events that led to the beginning of the Raiders from Typhon's point of view. Defend your kingdom from Halcyon and win great rewards. Call on your allies from the Invasion Box.

28.title: Asphodel Garrison
28.text: Enemy reinforcements have arrived! Can you stop them before they reach the gates of Asphodel? Request backup from the Reserves Box.

29.title: Asphodel Garrison
29.text: Put an end to the invasion on Asphodel once and for all! A Flurry of new cards are now available in the Conquer Box.

30.title: Asphodel Siege
30.text: Halcyon has cleared a path to Asphodel. March alongside him before Typhon returns to reinforce the legendary palace. Reap the benefits of the Bounty Box to take down Typhon or your enemies in the Frenzy Brawl, starting Friday.

31.title: Rise of the Imperials
31.text: Asphodel has fallen, and in its wake is nothing but a barren Wasteland and The Rise of the Imperials. Take part in this epic Guild War between titanic powers and sculpt your army from the Ascension Box to rise above the rest.

32.title: Alpha Rebirth
32.text: Progenitors lead an army comprised of all factions, including former comrades. Will this combined threat be too much to handle, or is it just a prelude to a much more dangerous enemy? Get all the help you can from the Revival Box in the store now.

33.title: Alpha Rebirth
33.text: Another pair wanders on the island of Progenitors. What mysterious powers will they find? Uncover these mysteries and conquer the island with the Dominion Box now in store.

34.title: Apocalypse Raid
34.text: Band together with your Guild to take on the mighty Apocalypse in the first Guild Raid, and Alpha Rebirth enters the final stage. Can you defeat this powerful foe? Grow your arsenal with the Rebirth Box in the store.

35.title: Metamorphosis War
35.text: The power of the Progenitors flows through the battlefield. Factions are able to harness the strength of rivals. Will you prevail in this super powered Guild War? Bring on a new era of dominance with the New Dawn Box now in the store.

36.title: Dimensional Terror
36.text: The Spire is under attack by a Xeno ground invasion! Recruit new units, featuring the new skill Overload, from the Breach Box in the store. Or test your might in the Enfeebling battleground effect of the Enclave Brawl.

37.title: Dimensional Terror
37.text: The Xeno continue to draw power from the Spire as they attempt to open a portal to their homeworld. Can you stop it before terrible monstrosities emerge? And prepare tomorrow for the Jotun Raid, featuring the new skill Valor!

38.title: Dimensional Terror
38.text: Arachis is beginning to emerge from the portal. Knock it back and close the portal for good! Then prepare your armies for the Multiverse Brawl beginning tomorrow. Overcome these adversities with help from the Vengeance Box in the store.

39.title: Forsaken
39.text: Fight through the Forsaken defenses and make your way to the Neurological Operating eXcavator to sever their Sulfuris technology. Build your strength up for the Reaping the Battlefield Guild War Event beginning tomorrow.

40.title: Forsaken
40.text: The Forsaken's ultimate weapon has been activated. Demolish Pandemonium before it brings about the destruction the Forsaken crave. Augment your forces with the Bionic Box in store now.

41.title: Forsaken Horde
41.text: Lead by the Reaper, the Forsaken Horde is a pack of vicious outcasts too deadly and crazy even for the Raiders. Wherever they go a trail of blood and gore is sure to follow. Band together with your Guild and take down this vicious Raid. Recruit new Commanders from new Mutant Missions.

42.title: Blood Harvest
42.text: The hordes of the Forsaken may have been defeated, but the ground beneath the feet of Tabitha and Octane has collapsed, trapping them in the caverns below the pits. Can they survive the packs of Bloodthirsty waiting for them? Help rescue them with the Crimson Box now in the store.

43.title: Blood Harvest
43.text: The fight for survival through the Cavern of Blood continues this week as the Imperials happen across an old friend deep within the Bloodthirsty lair. Help our heroes find their way out of this death trap using new cards in the Classified Box now in store! Be sure to join us tomorrow to take on Oluth in a brand new Raid.

44.title: Tabitha's Exile
44.text: Halcyon orders Tabitha to betray their allies for the good of the Imperials, she refuses and is sentenced to death. Help Tabitha fight back against this oppression and escape from Valhalla Station. Recruit new cards from the Loyalty Box to power up your forces!

45.title: Tabitha's Exile
45.text: Octane refuses to carry out his order to kill Tabitha and together they must escape The Intrepid. Can they survive? Defeat this powerful enemy with new cards in the Comrade Box.

46.title: Sins of the Divine
46.text: The Righteous are attempting to unearth a sinister device left behind by the Progenitors. Stop them before they unleash unknown power to change history forever.

47.title: Sins of the Divine
47.text: The Righteous successfully activated the ancient Progenitor technology, the Olympus Fragment. Help Octane and Tabitha quickly stop them from using its power to control time and space. Power up with new cards in the Blade Box!

48.title: Progenitor's Continuum
48.text: Tabitha and Octane set their sights on the Spire as they attempt to escape the Progenitor forces. Arm yourself with new forces in the Encompass Box!

49.title: Progenitor's Continuum
49.text: Tabitha and Octane's fight to get out of the Progenitor's Continuum becomes complicated when Tabitha succumbs to Mesmerize's mind control powers. Help Octane save Tabitha and escape the Progenitor's Continuum with new powerful cards in the Rex Box!

50.title: New Feature: Campaigns!
50.text: A new event this week featuring 7 tough fights with reserves and card death is taking place! To participate you must have beaten Mission 106 in the main storyline. There are three difficulties and each has its own reward set. Good luck!

51.title: Asphodel's End
51.text: Time travel back to the the beginning of the Raiders as Halcyon hunts down the remaining Asphodelians. Control the Nexus with new power in the Stalwart Box.

52.title: Asphodel's End
52.text: Typhon Vex is attempting to escape the Imperials reach as Halcyon's forces sweep over Asphodel. Stop his escape with new power in the Lotus Box.

53.title: Asphodel's End
53.text: The Brimstone has been called in to extract the Asphodelians. Crush their attempts in a brand new campaign featured in this final week of the event! New cards in the Explusion Box are available to help your quest.

54.title: Conquest
54.text: Conquer hostile regions of Acheron in a new Guild Free-For-All PVP event featuring a beautiful full 3D map! Evolve your Leech into the powerful new Refresh skill with the Refresh Cache.

55.title: Secrets
55.text: Deep within the tattered ruins of the crashed Worldship, now free from its Blight prison, a dark secret echoes for its master. The Righteous may be at the right place at the right time. Discover secret power in the the Recon Box!

56.title: Secrets
56.text: The Xeno are relentless in their scouring of their hidden technology, but what is it? Some sort of weapon? Constantine beckons Empress to find what the Xeno are looking for before it is too late. Assist them on their quest with new power in the Ambassador Box!

57.title: Secrets
57.text: The towering monstrosity Fury, brimming with power, is both a terrible obstacle and a godsend for the Righteous. Take it from the Xeno in a brand new Campaign "Secrets Revealed". Conquer this behemoth with new strength found in the Expedition Box!

58.title: Tartarus Crusade
58.text: The Righteous storm into Tartarus on a crusade to end the Bloodthirsty threat once and for all! Typhon Vex has other plans for the blight and sends Barracus to stop them. Stop the Righteous caravan with new cards in the Conflict Box!

59.title: Tartarus Crusade
59.text: The Righteous are bringing the Fury core into the heart of Tartarus to blow it to smithereens. Typhon Vex commands Barracus to stop them at all costs! End the Righteous assault with new power found in the Flash Box.

60.title: Tartarus Crusade
60.text: Hope for the Righteous crusade seems lost. Barracus must complete his mission and stamp them out, but the Deidon is a powerful force to be reckoned with. Fight it out in a brand new Campaign! Call for backup with new powerful cards in the Shield Box.

61.title: Gore Typhon
61.text: Typhon Vex is the only man to have actively sought assimilation by the Blight. With his new power, he commands a Raider and Bloodthirsty army that seeks to take revenge for the falling of Asphodel. Take Gore Typhon down in a brand new raid with help from the Jade Box!

62.title: Tartarus Vengeance
62.text: The Righteous have been defeated, but the Bloodthirsty are still swarming. Typhon Vex has lost control over the Blight and now Barracus has to escape with his life. What could be causing the Bloodthirsty to stop listening to Typhon? Can Barracus make it out alive? Help him escape with new powerful cards in the Entwine box!

63.title: Tartarus Vengeance
63.text: Something has awoken in the Heart of Tartarus: an ancient being from the deepest recesses of the Bloodthirsty hives. Barracus finds himself out of control of his own body due to the powerful being. Now it is up to Typhon to extract him and put the demons of Tartarus back to rest. Slay the Bloodthirsty hordes with new power in the Cloak box!

64.title: Kalihmah Campagin
64.text: The most ancient Bloodthirsty, Kalihmah, reaches out of the heart of Tartarus and beckons its kin to do its bidding. You may not be able to slay the beast, but you can stop its influence... for now. Put a stop to this menace with new cards in the Treachery Box!

65.title: Supremacy Raid
65.text: The Progenitors are the oldest beings in the known universe, and Uruk the Supreme is one of their oldest great forms. Although its origins are unknown, many speculate Uruk to be responsible for the ancient domination of the Progenitors over all life forms. Take on this powerful enemy in the Supremacy Raid!

66.title: Arctis Prison
66.text: Locked away deep within the most secure prison in Acheron, a powerful Righteous sage waits patiently for his freedom. His sentence is for life, but Constantine sends one of his best extraction agents to give the sage an early release. Escape from the Imperials with new cards in the Shackle Box!

67.title: Arctis Prison
67.text: Kathryn successfully breaks Emrys out of HyperSec but the alarms are sounding and they are being hunted down. The Warden has called in his very best to stop the Righteous in their tracks. Help them escape with new powerful cards in the Opal Box!

68.title: Arctis Prison
68.text: The Warden of Arctis HyperSec is as cruel as he is powerful. Taking the matter into his own hands he intends to make the Righteous witness the power of his Mech Battle Armor. Trash his technology and make your final escape with new cards in the Titan Box!

69.title: The Intrepid
69.text: The Intrepid represents the brilliance of Imperial Engineering as Halcyon's personal flagship. It is the harbinger of misfortune for those that face it on the battlefield. Face this symbol of Imperial might in a brand new raid. Call upon your own might with new units in the Palladium Box!

70.title: Harrowing Journey
70.text: Tabitha and Octane find themselves deep inside the Precursor Swamplands of the Progenitor's Continuum as they try to find a way back to their own time. What challenges await them? How will they get back? Help them find their way with brand new cards in the Champion Box!

71.title: Harrowing Journey
71.text: Tabitha sets her sights on a mysterious Progenitor structure in the distance, while Octane sets his on the largest foe he can find. Defeat the monsters surrounding our heroes so they can investigate the structure with new powerful cards in the Brawn Box!

72.title: Harrowing Journey
72.text: The search for a way home continues for Tabitha and Octane as they get to the heart of the Swamplands at the doorstep of a mysterious structure with untold power. Fend off against the powerful threats and unlock the mystery of The Gateway with powerful new versions of old favorite cards in the Ancestor Box!
